==Ancient Greek==

===Etymology===
*Of Hebrew origin [[מרים]] {{HH|4813}};

===Pronunciation===
*Μαρία, Μαριάμ /  Maria  Mariam / mar-ee'-ah, mar-ee-am'

===Proper noun===
'''Μαρία'''

# Maria or Mariam (that is, Mirjam), the name of six Christian females: - [[Mary]].

